<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1910-01-20T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1910-01-20T00:00:00-05:00" n="82" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d82">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 4727/39 A.</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Brazilian Chargé</gloss>.</hi></head>
                        <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1910-01-20"><hi rend="italic">January 20,
                                1910</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                        <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I beg to confirm in writing what Mr. Hale,
                            at my request, stated to you orally, that the President will be pleased
                            to place his yacht, the <hi rend="italic">Mayflower</hi>, at your
                            disposal on the afternoon of Monday, <pb facs="0224" n="112" xml:id="pg_112"/> February 14, to convey the remains of the late
                            Ambassador Nabuco from Washington to Hampton Roads, where the remains
                            will be transferred to the cruiser <hi rend="italic">Montana</hi>, which
                            will convey them, escorted by yourself, to Rio de Janeiro.</p>
                        <p>Accept, etc.,</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">P. C. Knox.</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>